&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Frequency and reporting&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Planned Value estimates are provided at the beginning of each iteration. Earned Values are reported at the end of each&#xD;
    iteration. The Earned versus Actual Cost/ Effort chart is reviewed with the team during each iteration retrospective&#xD;
    and discussed with stakeholders to help identify trends.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Collection and reporting tools&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; Project Conductor&amp;reg; (version 2.0 and below)&amp;nbsp;collects cost data.&amp;nbsp;Effort data is collected in&#xD;
    IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; Team Concert&amp;reg;. IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; Insight&amp;reg; reports on this metric at the executive level.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Pitfalls, advice, and countermeasures&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Do not compare effort to cost, but compare planned financial cost to actual financial cost or planned effort to&#xD;
        actual effort.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Use this metric to track cost / effort performance &lt;u>compared to the plan&lt;/u>&amp;nbsp;during the lifecycle.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Earned Value management is not an effective approach&amp;nbsp;for projects in which the requirements are not&#xD;
        stable,&amp;nbsp;or projects that&amp;nbsp;are not able to plan cost and schedule completion. If there are changes to the&#xD;
        plan, planned cost and earned value must be updated.&lt;br />&#xD;
        &lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></mainDescription>
